canonical:
  title: 李時敏讓給事中不允
  author: 崔惟淸
  language: lzh
  text: 爾相門冢嗣后掖近親幼藉敎忠之規長無挾貴之失端明謹潔行己有方幹敏恪勤守官以道累經煩使藹著休聲是用擢置瑣闈俾光省署擧因衆允恩匪爾私卽宜竭節以循公豈或執謙而苟免命不可易往其懋哉
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 李時敏讓給事中不允
  author: 崔惟淸
  language: lzh
  text: 爾相門冢嗣。后掖近親。幼藉敎忠之規。長無挾貴之失。端明謹潔。行己有方。幹敏恪勤。守官以道。累經煩使。藹著休聲。是用擢置瑣闈。俾光省署。擧因衆允。恩匪爾私。卽宜竭節以循公。豈或執謙而苟免。命不可易。往其懋哉。
korean:
  title: 이시민 양 급사중 불윤
  author: 최유청
  language: kor
  text: 너는 정승 가문의 맏아들이요 왕후의 가까운 친족으로서, 어려서부터 충성을 다하는 교육을 받았고, 자라서는 귀한 신분을 뽐내는 과실이 없었다. 단정하고 분명하고 삼가고 깨끗하여 몸을 닦는 것이 법이 있었고, 일을 봄에 성의 있고 부지런하여 관직을 책임대로 이행하였으며, 여러 번 고된 일을 맡겼으되 훌륭한 성적을 드러내었다. 이에 측근의 요직에 발탁하여 그 관서(官署)를 빛내게 하였다. 이는 뭇 사람들의 여론에 따라 임용한 것이요, 네게 사사로이 은전을 베풀려 함이 아니로다. 그러니 충절을 다하여 공사(公事)에 충실하여야 할 것이다. 어찌 겸양을 고집하여 구차히 이를 면하려 하는가. 임명을 고칠 수 없으니 곧바로 직에 나아가라.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0320_020_0220&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: On Li Shi-min's Refusal of the Position of Attendant Censor
  author: Choe Yoo-cheong
  language: eng
  text: You are the eldest son of a chancellor's house and close kin to the royal family. From youth you received instruction in loyalty and duty, and as you grew, you showed no arrogance born of noble station. Upright and clear in character, prudent and pure in conduct—your self-cultivation follows proper form. In your labors you show sincerity and diligence, fulfilling your office with integrity. Through many arduous tasks you have proven yourself, earning renown for excellence. Thus we elevate you to this intimate post, that you might bring honor to this bureau. This appointment follows the will of many voices, not favor granted for private gain. Therefore you must dedicate yourself wholly to the public good, serving with unflinching loyalty. How could you cling to false modesty and seek to escape your duty? The decree cannot be changed. Go forth and excel in your charge.
  footnotes:
    - This is a formal appointment edict addressing someone named Li Shi-min who had apparently declined the position of Attendant Censor (급사중), a court office of considerable prestige and responsibility.
    - The 'chancellor's house' (정승 가문) and 'close kin to the royal family' indicate Li came from the highest aristocratic circles of Goryeo society.
    - The phrase about 'intimate post' (측근의 요직) refers to positions in the royal secretariat or inner court, positions of both honor and delicate responsibility.
